\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Log-log degree distributions for the three Higgs Twitter networks (rows: Mention, Reply, Retweet), showing in-degree (left) and out-degree (right). All three exhibit heavy-tailed in-degree distributions consistent with preferential-attachment dynamics. Out-degree distributions are considerably more concentrated, indicating that most users participate moderately while a small number act as prolific broadcasters.}}{4}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:higgs_deg}{{2}{4}{Log-log degree distributions for the three Higgs Twitter networks (rows: Mention, Reply, Retweet), showing in-degree (left) and out-degree (right). All three exhibit heavy-tailed in-degree distributions consistent with preferential-attachment dynamics. Out-degree distributions are considerably more concentrated, indicating that most users participate moderately while a small number act as prolific broadcasters}{figure.caption.3}{}}
